                            <comment id="16752846" author="githubbot" created="Sat, 26 Jan 2019 00:23:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;rhauch commented on pull request #6203: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7873&quot; title=&quot;KafkaBasedLog&amp;#39;s consumer should always seek to beginning when starting&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-7873&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-7873&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Always seek to beginning in KafkaBasedLog&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6203&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6203&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   Explicitly seek KafkaBasedLog&#8217;s consumer to the beginning of the topic partitions, rather than potentially use committed offsets (which would be unexpected) if group.id is set or rely upon `auto.offset.reset=earliest` if the group.id is null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   This should not change existing behavior but should remove some potential issues introduced with KIP-287 if `group.id` is not set in the consumer configurations. Note that even if `group.id` is set, we still always want to consume from the beginning.&lt;/p&gt;

